DualPathBaseline
================

Topology
- hostA -> r1 -> r2 -> r3 -> hostB
- backup branch: r1 -> r4 -> r3

Routing
- Primary path: hostA -> r1 -> r2 -> r3 -> hostB
- Backup path: hostA -> r1 -> r4 -> r3 -> hostB
- OSPF interface costs prefer the r1-r2-r3 branch and keep the r1-r4-r3 branch as a higher-cost alternative.

Goal
- Provide the smallest clean dissertation baseline for dual-path routing.
- Establish a deterministic OSPF topology before adding failures, proactive rerouting logic, or custom code.
